on.\r\n\r\nAdded bonus, the new release is unisex, making it an excellent present for anyone in your life (you).\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://triumphanddisaster.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">triumphanddisaster.com.au</a>','Triumph & Disaster has released a unisex toner','','inherit','closed','closed','','1053-revision-v1','','','2017-09-26 03:07:24','2017-09-26 03:07:24','',1053,'http://localhost/uncategorized/1053-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1056,4,'2017-09-26 03:09:25','2017-09-26 03:09:25','<div>\r\n\r\nIt’s not just our wardrobes that brighten up come summer. We’re all for experimenting with makeup and testing out bold new looks. And we decided to do just that in our September issue.\r\n\r\nLucky for you, makeup artist Rob Povey and hair stylists Tanya Grant and Ryan Brown from Joey Scandizzo Salon compiled their notes, so you can get the look too.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div><strong>Skin </strong></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\nHana’s skin was prepped with a liberal application of MAC <a href=\"http://www.maccosmetics.com.au/product/13825/967/products/skincare/primers/prep-prime-skin\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Prep + Prime Fix</a> and MAC <a href=\"http://www.maccosmetics.com.au/product/13824/364/products/skincare/moisturisers/strobe-cream#/shade/Silverlite_\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Strobe Cream</a> in Goldlite. It was then evened out using MAC <a href=\"http://www.maccosmetics.com.au/product/13847/32554/products/makeup/face/foundation/studio-face-and-body-foundation-120-ml#/shade/N1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Studio Face and Body Foundation</a>, and MAC<a href=\"http://www.maccosmetics.com.au/product/13825/15746/products/skincare/primers/prepprime-highlighter#/shade/Dark\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> Prep + Prime Highlighter</a> to bounce light and diffuse imperfections.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cheeks </strong>\r\n\r\nCheeks were sculpted using MAC <a href=\"http://www.maccosmetics.com.au/product/13848/316/products/makeup/face/multi-use/cream-colour-base#/shade/Pearl\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cream Colour Base</a> in Midtone Sepia, and MAC <a href=\"http://www.maccosmetics.com.au/product/13824/45697/products/skincare/moisturisers/prep-prime-essential-oils-stick\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Prep + Prime Essential Oils Stick</a> pressed into the high planes to create a dewy sheen.\r\n\r\n<strong>Brows </strong>\r\n\r\nBrows were pre-lightened with bleach, and brushed up with MAC <a href=\"http://www.maccosmetics.com.au/product/13834/305/products/makeup/eyes/brow/brow-set#/shade/Clear\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Clear Brow Set</a> for a full, fluffy texture.\r\n\r\n<strong>Eyes </strong>\r\n\r\nMAC <a href=\"http://www.maccosmetics.com.au/product/13848/316/products/makeup/face/multi-use/cream-colour-base#/shade/Pearl\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cream Colour Base </a>in Yellow Scream and Rich Coral was buffed over the entire lid and into the brow bone for a creamy wash of colour. MAC <a href=\"http://www.maccosmetics.com.au/product/13840/32245/products/makeup/eyes/shadow/studio-eye-gloss#/shade/Médoc_\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Studio Eye Gloss</a> in Pearl Varnish was tapped on top to create a glossy look. Lashes were curled, but no mascara was used.\r\n\r\n<strong>Lips </strong>\r\n\r\nLips were given a soft, understated pink tint to offset the bold eyes using MAC <a href=\"http://www.maccosmetics.com.au/product/13854/52594/products/makeup/lips/lipstick/glaze-lipstick#/shade/Hot_Tahiti\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Glaze Lipstick</a> in Hue and MAC <a href=\"http://www.maccosmetics.com.au/product/13853/255/products/makeup/lips/lip-gloss/clear-lipglass\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Clear Lipglass</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Hair </strong>\r\n\r\nTo add a soft texture, Hana’s hair was prepped with ELEVEN Australia’s <a href=\"http://elevenaustralia.com/product/miracle-hair-treatment/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Miracle Hair Treatment</a> and <a href=\"http://elevenaustralia.com/product/sea-salt-texture-spray/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sea Salt Texture Spray</a>.\r\n\r\nELEVEN Australia <a href=\"http://elevenaustralia.com/product/give-me-hold-flexible-hairspray/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Give Me Hold Flexible Hairspray</a> was used to create a brushed-back look, while still keeping the hair’s natural texture and movement.\r\n\r\nWe experimented with different styles and parting throughout this shoot, so it was really important to use lightweight styling products like ELEVEN Australia’s Sea Salt Texture Spray and Give Me Hold Flexible Hairspray.\r\n\r\nTo highlight Hana’s blonde hair, shine was added using ELEVEN Australia’s<a href=\"http://elevenaustralia.com/product/smooth-shine-anti-frizz-serum/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> Smooth and Shine Anti-Frizz Serum</a>.\r\n\r\n<em>Check out the full shoot <a href=\"http://fashionjournal.com.au//fashion/shoots/fj-shoot-drift\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a>.</em>\r\n<div><strong>Photography:</strong> Amelia J Dowd at Sync Production and Management\r\n<strong>Styling:</strong> Jam Baylon\r\n<strong>Hair:</strong> Tanya Grant and Ryan Brown at Joey Scandizzo Salon using Eleven Australia\r\n<strong>Makeup: </strong>Rob Povey using Mac Cosmetics\r\n<strong>Model:</strong> Hana at Fivetwenty Model Management</div>','How to get our September cover look','','publish','open','open','','how-to-get-our-september-cover-look','','','2017-09-26 03:09:25','2017-09-26 03:09:25','',0,'http://localhost/?p=1056',0,'post','',0),(1057,4,'2017-09-26 03:09:09','2017-09-26 03:09:09','','8O4A9241 as Smart Object-1_3','','inherit','open','closed','','8o4a9241-as-smart-object-1_3','','','2017-09-26 03:09:09','2017-09-26 03:09:09','',1056,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/8O4A9241-as-Smart-Object-1_3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1058,4,'2017-09-26 03:09:25','2017-09-26 03:09:25','<div>\r\n\r\nIt’s not just our wa