trong>How it feels/smells/looks</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Like all GlamGlow products, the Volcasmic Moisturizer packaging is super cute. The scent is quite sweet, giving off notes of orange and vanilla. It feels light and soft on the skin, but the pressed form means it’s a little more balmy than creamy.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Why I like it</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The moisturiser glides on easily, and a little goes a long way. It provides a nice glow underneath your makeup, making it perfect primer substitute to get a dewy look. Also love the scent every time I open the jar.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Areas for improvement</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As someone with oily skin, this product didn’t quite mattify my T-Zone. I felt that it was too balmy as a daily moisturiser. However it worked really nicely as a night treatment and kept my makeup intact during the day.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Final comments</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">It’s a great product but would probably work differently on different skin types. If you’re on the hunt for a moisturiser that doubles as a radiant primer, it’s worth looking into.</p>','Beauty report: GlamGlow Volcasmic Matte Glow Moisturizer','','publish','open','open','','beauty-report-glamglow-volcasmic-matte-glow-moisturizer','','','2017-09-26 03:16:09','2017-09-26 03:16:09','',0,'http://localhost/?p=1073',0,'post','',0),(1074,4,'2017-09-26 03:15:56','2017-09-26 03:15:56','','GlamGlowMoisturiser','','inherit','open','closed','','glamglowmoisturiser','','','2017-09-26 03:15:56','2017-09-26 03:15:56','',1073,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/GlamGlowMoisturiser.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1075,4,'2017-09-26 03:16:09','2017-09-26 03:16:09','<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Name:</strong> GlamGlow Volcasmic Matte Glow Moisturizer\r\n<strong>Price: </strong>$79\r\n<strong>What it does:</strong> A lightweight, pressed moisturiser that hydrates the skin while absorbing natural oils to maintain a ma