l level. Made in Australia, Gemma’s range is cruelty-free and sans palm and mineral oil, parabens, synthetic fragrances and nanoparticles.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.gemmavendetta.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">gemmavendetta.com.au</a>','7 natural beauty brands you need in your bathroom cabinet','','inherit','closed','closed','','1101-revision-v1','','','2017-09-26 03:40:43','2017-09-26 03:40:43','',1101,'http://localhost/uncategorized/1101-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1110,4,'2017-09-26 03:42:09','2017-09-26 03:42:09','Lipslut is proving that makeup can change more than just your face.\r\n\r\nUntil the end of August, Lipslut will donate 100 per cent of the proceeds from its F*ck Trump Lipstick to those affected by the Charlottesville attack.\r\n\r\nCreated by college student Kati Sones, Lipslut started its F*ck Trump campaign to protest Trump’s presidency, making donations to US charities including the American Civil Liberties Union, The Centre For Reproductive Rights, Planned Parenthood, and the National Organisation for Women.\r\n\r\nHowever, since one woman was killed and 19 others were injured when a car driven by a white supremacist slammed into counter protesters last weekend, the brand has changed its approach.\r\n\r\nDonations will be made to individual victims and their families, as well as charity groups such as the Albemarle-Charlottesville NAACP and Charlottesville\'s Black Lives Matter organisation.\r\n\r\nLipslut F*ck Trump Pink Matte Liquid Lipstick is available at<a href=\"https://www.lipslut.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> Lipslut</a> for $19.95 (USD)\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://lipslut.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">lipslut.com</a>','This lipstick is raising money for the victims of the Charlottesville attack','','publish','open','open','','this-lipstick-is-raising-money-for-the-victims-of-the-charlottesville-attack','','','2017-09-26 03:42:09','2017-09-26 03:42:09','',0,'http://localhost/?p=1110',0,'post',''